{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "coupled_refresh_regrid",
    "description": "Shared offline fixture for the cross-language REFRESH-PATH conformance (CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.10). A discretized, COUPLED, non-PDE model whose forcing is read from data loaders at a discrete cadence and REGRIDDED from the loader's coarse 6-cell native grid onto the 3-cell simulation grid — IN-MODEL, as a coupling expression, not through a regrid seam. The 2:1 area-weighted coarsening is a const weight matrix `W[i,j]` (an in-file `const` observed): `F_tgt[j] = sum_i W[i,j]*F_src[i]`, `scale_tgt[j] = sum_i W[i,j]*scale_src[i]`. `F_src` is DISCRETE — its loader `emis` declares a `temporal` block, so it refreshes at the hourly cadence anchors and the regridded `F_tgt` is a DISCRETE-materialized field (state-free but forcing-tainted). `scale_src` is CONST — its loader `factors` has no `temporal`, so it materializes once and the regridded `scale_tgt` is CONST-cadence. The coupled states integrate the regridded forcing: `D(c[j]) = scale_tgt[j]*F_tgt[j]` (the forced tracer) and `D(d[j]) = c[j]` (a dependent variable integrating the tracer across the cadence). The forcing is piecewise-constant across the cadence segments, so the regridded arrays and the integrated trajectory are closed-form and checkable to solver tolerance — the analytic golden lives in golden/coupled_refresh_regrid.json. TWO-VIEW contract (RFC pure-io-data-loaders §4.6): the loader-fed `F_src`/`scale_src` are declared `discrete`+`data_ingest` here so the cadence classifier resolves them CONST/DISCRETE, but the typed array-simulate compiler has no Discrete VariableType — a consumer STRIPS the loader-fed discrete declarations before compiling the RHS, where `F_src`/`scale_src` then resolve through the forcing buffer refreshed at each cadence anchor. There is NO regrid seam / RegridApplier (removed as obsolete in v0.8.0): regridding is an ordinary in-model coupling contraction over the native forcing.",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciAST/polecats/gastown.furiosa"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "refresh-path",
      "loader-seeded",
      "data-loader",
      "temporal",
      "discrete-variable",
      "regrid",
      "in-model-regrid",
      "conservative",
      "cadence",
      "coupled",
      "conformance"
    ]
  },
  "data_loaders": {
    "emis": {
      "kind": "grid",
      "source": {
        "url_template": "file:///data/emis/src_{date:%Y%m%d%H}.nc"
      },
      "temporal": {
        "frequency": "PT1H",
        "file_period": "P1D",
        "records_per_file": 24
      },
      "variables": {
        "F_src": {
          "file_variable": "surface_source",
          "units": "kg/s",
          "description": "Time-varying loader-fed source field on the coarse 6-cell native grid, refreshed every hour as the loader advances to the next record. Its `temporal` block makes the loader output DISCRETE (RFC pure-io-data-loaders §4.6). Regridded in-model onto the 3-cell sim grid by the `W` contraction (`F_tgt`)."
        }
      }
    },
    "factors": {
      "kind": "grid",
      "source": {
        "url_template": "file:///data/factors/scale.nc"
      },
      "variables": {
        "scale_src": {
          "file_variable": "scale_factor",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Static per-cell scale factor on the coarse 6-cell native grid. Its loader has NO `temporal` block, so the partition seeds it CONST (materialized once). Regridded in-model onto the 3-cell sim grid by the `W` contraction (`scale_tgt`)."
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "models": {
    "M": {
      "variables": {
        "W": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "shape": ["src_cells", "tgt_cells"],
          "description": "Const conservative-regrid weight matrix W[i,j] (i=1..6 native source cells, j=1..3 sim target cells): the 2:1 area-weighted coarsening. Each target cell j averages its two source cells (W=0.5), so W is the in-model realization of the native->sim regrid. A build-once const observed.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "const",
            "args": [],
            "value": [
              [0.5, 0.0, 0.0],
              [0.5, 0.0, 0.0],
              [0.0, 0.5, 0.0],
              [0.0, 0.5, 0.0],
              [0.0, 0.0, 0.5],
              [0.0, 0.0, 0.5]
            ]
          }
        },
        "F_src": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "refresh": { "kind": "data_ingest", "source": "emis" },
          "description": "Loader-fed source read from the `emis` DataLoader (WITH temporal): DISCRETE cadence, refreshed at each hourly anchor on the 6-cell native grid. Resolves through the forcing buffer in the typed RHS after the loader-discrete strip."
        },
        "scale_src": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "refresh": { "kind": "data_ingest", "source": "factors" },
          "description": "Loader-fed scale factor read from the `factors` DataLoader (NO temporal): CONST cadence, materialized once on the 6-cell native grid. Resolves through the forcing buffer in the typed RHS after the loader-discrete strip."
        },
        "F_tgt": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/s",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "In-model regridded source on the 3-cell sim grid: F_tgt[j] = sum_i W[i,j]*F_src[i]. State-free but DISCRETE-forcing-tainted (reads F_src), so it materializes once per cadence refresh — the in-model regrid is the DISCRETE-materialized field.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 6], "j": [1, 3] },
            "args": [],
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                { "op": "index", "args": ["W", "i", "j"] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["F_src", "i"] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        "scale_tgt": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "In-model regridded scale on the 3-cell sim grid: scale_tgt[j] = sum_i W[i,j]*scale_src[i]. Reads only const W and the CONST loader scale_src, so it is CONST-cadence (materialized once).",
          "expression": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 6], "j": [1, 3] },
            "args": [],
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                { "op": "index", "args": ["W", "i", "j"] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["scale_src", "i"] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        "c": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Integrated tracer concentration on the sim grid — CONTINUOUS cadence (changes every step). D(c[j]) = scale_tgt[j]*F_tgt[j], the regridded forcing."
        },
        "d": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Integrated coupled tracer — CONTINUOUS. D(d[j]) = c[j]; a dependent variable integrating the forced tracer across the cadence, coupled to c."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(c[j]) = scale_tgt[j]*F_tgt[j]. scale_tgt is CONST (const loader, materialized once); F_tgt is DISCRETE (temporal loader, refreshed per anchor). Both are in-model regrids of the 6-cell native fields onto j in [1,3]. Dense [1,3] ranges (not {from:<set>}) — index_sets are not yet carried through flatten.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "j": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["c", "j"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "j": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                { "op": "index", "args": ["scale_tgt", "j"] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["F_tgt", "j"] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "D(d[j]) = c[j]. The coupling: d integrates the forced tracer c.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "j": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["d", "j"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": { "j": [1, 3] },
            "expr": { "op": "index", "args": ["c", "j"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
